The paper is about motion planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to identify critical regions for motion planning suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of CNNs for image processing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed approach on challenging motion planning problems, which suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
